---
import Article from '../../layouts/Article.astro';
import { SITE } from '../../lib/site';

const description = `Privacy policy for ${SITE.name} — what we collect, ads, affiliate links, and how quote/contact form data may be shared with partners.`;
---

<Article
  title="Privacy policy"
  description={description}
  crumbs={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Privacy' }]}
  updated="2026-07-12"
  showMiniBoard={false}
>
  <p>Last updated: 12 July 2026. Operator: {SITE.name}. Contact: {SITE.contactEmail}.</p>

  <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    {SITE.name} ({SITE.url}) is an Australian information website about solar and home batteries. This
    policy explains how we handle personal information under the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth) and the Australian
    Privacy Principles.
  </p>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Contact and quote forms:</strong> name, email, and (for quote requests) phone, postcode, and
      consent records. Message text if you use the contact form.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Server and security logs:</strong> IP address, user agent, and basic request metadata via
      Cloudflare, used for security, rate limiting, and diagnosing faults. We do not use these logs to
      build marketing profiles.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Analytics:</strong> Cloudflare Web Analytics (privacy-oriented, no advertising cookies from
      that beacon alone).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Advertising:</strong> if Google AdSense or similar is enabled, those providers may set cookies
      or use identifiers subject to their own policies.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we use information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To respond to contact messages</li>
    <li>To process quote requests and connect you with installers or quoting partners (when that service is active)</li>
    <li>To secure the site and prevent spam (including Cloudflare Turnstile)</li>
    <li>To understand aggregate traffic and improve content</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Quote leads and sharing with partners</h2>
  <p>
    When you submit a quote request and tick the consent box, you agree that {SITE.name} and up to three
    installers or quoting partners may contact you by phone, SMS or email about your request. Lead details
    may be shared with those partners for that purpose — this is how a future quote-referral revenue line
    would work. We use a CRM workflow (GoHighLevel or equivalent) to store and route submissions.
  </p>
  <p>
    We will not sell your contact details for unrelated marketing lists. Partners must comply with the Spam
    Act 2003 (Cth): identifiable sender, consent basis, and a functional unsubscribe for marketing messages.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies and ads</h2>
  <p>
    Essential delivery uses Cloudflare. Ad partners may use cookies or local storage. Affiliate links are
    commercial; they do not require your contact details by themselves.
  </p>

  <h2>Retention and security</h2>
  <p>
    Form submissions are retained as long as needed to fulfil the request, meet legal obligations, and
    resolve disputes, then deleted or de-identified. We use HTTPS and provider access controls; no method
    of transmission is perfectly secure.
  </p>

  <h2>Access and correction</h2>
  <p>
    Email {SITE.contactEmail} to request access to, or correction of, personal information we hold about you. You
    may also complain to the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner if you are not satisfied
    with our response.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy; the date above will change. Material changes affecting lead sharing will be
    reflected here before the public quote form is promoted in navigation.
  </p>
</Article>
